---
/**
 * /about — what 4thewin is and who built it.
 * Static prose page. Same layout template as /privacy and /terms.
 */
import RootLayout from "~/layouts/RootLayout.astro";
---

<RootLayout title="4thewin — About" description="What 4thewin is and who built it.">
  <main
    id="main"
    class="mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl flex-1 overflow-y-auto px-margin-mobile pt-[126px] pb-16 md:pt-[140px]"
  >
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-3">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground md:text-5xl">
        About
      </h1>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-col gap-10">
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-foreground/80">
          <span class="font-display italic text-foreground">4thewin</span> is a
          web-based Connect 4 platform: play against a smart AI right in your
          browser, or sign up to challenge other players online, track your
          stats, chat, and climb the leaderboard.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">The project</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-foreground/80">
          It's the final group project of the 42 Common Core — a full-stack web
          app built from scratch: real-time multiplayer over WebSockets, an AI
          opponent using minimax with alpha-beta pruning, user accounts, a
          friends system, in-app chat and notifications, all behind a hardened
          security layer.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Under the hood</h2>
        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2 text-foreground/80">
          <li class="leading-relaxed">
            <span class="font-semibold text-foreground">Frontend</span> — Astro + React, Tailwind CSS.
          </li>
          <li class="leading-relaxed">
            <span class="font-semibold text-foreground">Backend</span> — Fastify, Socket.io, PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM.
          </li>
          <li class="leading-relaxed">
            <span class="font-semibold text-foreground">Security</span> — ModSecurity WAF, HashiCorp Vault, JWT auth.
          </li>
          <li class="leading-relaxed">
            <span class="font-semibold text-foreground">Infra</span> — Podman containers, single-command deploy.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">The team</h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-foreground/80">
          Built by a team of 42 students, each owning a slice of the stack:
          backend, frontend, cybersecurity, and project management.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</RootLayout>
